<p class="article-lead">International perfume shipping options are constrained by dangerous-goods acceptance. Compare routes by eligibility and total landed outcome before comparing transit time.</p><h2>Courier or air freight</h2><p>May suit samples or urgent commercial shipments when the carrier and route accept the classification. Minimum charges and specialist handling can be significant.</p><h2>Sea freight</h2><p>Can suit larger orders, but consolidation rules, port handling, documentation and destination charges require advance planning.</p><p>For every option, confirm shipper responsibilities, packing, insurance, customs documents, importer readiness and last-mile delivery. Ask for a written quotation tied to the actual quantity and route; “door to door” should not be interpreted as unconditional customs or compliance responsibility.</p>
